woeful /ˈwəʊfəl/

1. ADJ If someone or something is woeful , they are very sad. 悲伤的 

例： ...a woeful ballad. …一支悲伤的歌谣。 

2. woefully ADV 悲伤地 [ADV with v] 

例： He said woefully: 'I love my country, but it does not give a damn about me.' 他悲伤地说：“我爱我的国家，但是它压根就不在乎我。” 

3. ADJ You can use woeful to emphasize that something is very bad or undesirable. 糟糕透顶的 [journalism] 

例： ...the woeful state of the economy. …这种糟糕透顶的经济状况。 

4. woefully ADV 糟糕透顶地 

例： Public expenditure on the arts is woefully inadequate. 艺术上的公共支出严重不足。

